[2026-03-19T08:24:28.896Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Execute this requirement immediately without asking questions.\n\n## REQUIREMENT\n\n# Classify OAuth errors by type for pattern detection\n\n## Metadata\n- **Category**: code_quality\n- **Effort**: High (3/3)\n- **Impact**: Unknown (7/3)\n- **Scan Type**: observability_scout\n- **Generated**: 3/18/2026, 7:32:55 PM\n\n## Description\nReplace the generic error logging in postTokenEndpoint with structured error classification. Parse HTTP status codes and response bodies to categorize failures into: invalid_grant (refresh token consumed/expired, re-auth required), rate_limited (429, back off), server_error (5xx, transient), network_error (fetch throw, transient), and invalid_request (400, bug). Log each error with a classified errorType field and emit it in metrics. This enables operators to distinguish between transient issues that self-heal and permanent failures requiring user re-authentication.\n\n## Reasoning\nCurrently postTokenEndpoint logs status and raw error text, which is hard to aggregate or alert on. A 401 invalid_grant (meaning the user must re-authorize) looks identical in logs to a transient 503 from Anthropic. Error classification lets operators set up targeted alerts and helps developers quickly determine the correct remediation path.\n\n\n## Recommended Skills\n\n- **compact-ui-design**: Use `.claude/skills/compact-ui-design.md` for high-quality UI design references and patterns\n\n## Notes\n\nThis requirement was generated from an AI-evaluated project idea. No specific goal is associated with this idea.\n\n## DURING IMPLEMENTATION\n\n- Use `get_memory` MCP tool when you encounter unfamiliar code or need context about patterns/files\n- Use `report_progress` MCP tool at each major phase (analyzing, planning, implementing, testing, validating)\n- Use `get_related_tasks` MCP tool before modifying shared files to check for parallel task conflicts\n\n## AFTER IMPLEMENTATION\n\n1. Log your implementation using the `log_implementation` MCP tool with:\n   - requirementName: the requirement filename (without .md)\n   - title: 2-6 word summary\n   - overview: 1-2 paragraphs describing what was done\n   - category: one of feature/bugfix/refactor/performance/security/infrastructure/ui/docs/test\n   - patternsApplied: comma-separated patterns used (e.g. \"repository pattern, debounce, memoization\")\n\n2. Verify: `npx tsc --noEmit` (fix any type errors)\n\nBegin implementation now."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d3723eba-4b01-4936-8e79-68e61fc0bca1","uuid":"e8aeba33-fa49-4c1c-84ed-02523c71b7dc","timestamp":"2026-03-19T08:24:28.792Z","isSynthetic":true}
