[2026-03-19T08:25:17.741Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01Dtint69YX6osHSKTPe24Qp","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture. The code already has:\n\n1. `OAuthErrorType` type with all 5 categories\n2. `OAuthError` interface with errorType, status, message, transient, raw\n3. `classifyHttpError()` and `classifyNetworkError()` functions\n4. `TokenEndpointResult` discriminated union\n5. `postTokenEndpoint()` uses classification, structured logging with `errorType` and `transient` fields\n6. Audit log recording with errorType on failures\n7. HTTP handlers mapping classified errors to appropriate HTTP status codes\n\nWhat's missing according to the requirement:\n\n\n- **Error metrics by type** — The `OAuthFunnelMetrics` interface only tracks flow-level metrics (started/completed/expired/failed), but doesn't break down errors by `OAuthErrorType`. The requirement says to \"emit it in metrics\" — meaning we need counters per error type exposed in the metrics/health endpoint.\n\nSo I need to add per-error-type counters to `OAuthManager`, increment them in `postTokenEndpoint` when errors are classified, expose them via a new method or extend `OAuthFunnelMetrics`, and surface them in the health endpoint.\n\nThe health endpoint doesn't currently expose OAuth funnel metrics — I see `oauth.hasTokens()` in the health check and more details in the status handler. I'll need to create an `OAuthErrorMetrics` interface with per-error-type counters, add private counters to `OAuthManager`, increment them when errors are classified in `postTokenEndpoint`, add a `getErrorMetrics()` method, and expose it in the health endpoint under `dependencies.oauth`. I also need to make sure `flowsFailed` is incremented on token endpoint failures like code exchange and refresh token failures.\n\nNow I'm checking how `flowsCompleted` and `flowsFailed` are currently being tracked...\n\nLooking at `exchangeCode`, I see `flowsFailed` increments when state isn't found or is expired, but there's a gap: when `postTokenEndpoint` succeeds, `flowsCompleted` never increments, and when it fails, `flowsFailed` never increments either. That's worth noting but not the immediate focus — the main issue is that error metrics broken down by type aren't being tracked anywhere.\n\nI'll add an error metrics interface to track failures by classification, create private counters in `OAuthManager`, increment them when errors occur in `postTokenEndpoint`, expose them through a getter method, and wire that into the health endpoint. While I'm at it, I should fix the funnel metrics so `flowsCompleted` actually gets incremented on successful token exchange, since that's directly tied to the error classification work I'm doing.\n\nActually, let me stay focused on what the requirement asks for — classifying OAuth errors by type for pattern detection. The funnel metrics gap is a separate issue, though fixing `flowsCompleted` is a straightforward bug I should address while I'm in this code.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":623,"cache_read_input_tokens":47973,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":623},"output_tokens":9,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d3723eba-4b01-4936-8e79-68e61fc0bca1","uuid":"38874443-c62f-4ec1-9579-8ba9f9312cd9"}
